I"}<h3 id="description">Description</h3>
<p>Design a responsive, three page site for a fictional retail company. You will create the company name and branding as well as curate a selection of goods the company sells prior to the design of the site. The site must have:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A home page – Introduces the company and the kinds of goods it sells and shows some of the inventory</li>
  <li>A product page – Shows a specific item that has at least 2 different variations for the customer to select. Examples of variations could be color and size if it was clothing, material and color if it was furniture.</li>
  <li>A third page that you decide on – Options could be a cart, rewards program, customer login page, about page, etc.). The content of this page will depend on the kind of page you select.</li>
  <li>A footer – Each page should have a footer that provides relevant information about the company.</li>
  <li>A navigation – Each page should have navigation to get you from one page to the next.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="requirements">Requirements</h4>
<ul>
  <li>At least 3 pages</li>
  <li>Navigation</li>
  <li>Mobile (320px) interactive prototype</li>
  <li>Tablet (768px) designs</li>
  <li>Desktop (1440px) interactive prototype</li>
  <li>Brief style guide that includes fonts, colors, and any graphic elements or treatments</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="checkpoints">Checkpoints</h3>
<ul>
  <li>February 25: Start</li>
  <li>March 4: 3 proposed companies with potential products</li>
  <li>March 11: Spring Break</li>
  <li>March 18: 10 logo options, colors, fonts, images, items, and inspiration for brand</li>
  <li>March 25: Style guide and wireframes for the home page at all sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)</li>
  <li>April 1: First draft of home page (all sizes), components and styles in Figma</li>
  <li>April 8: Further refined home page (all sizes), first draft of product page (all sizes)</li>
  <li>April 15: Further refined home and product pages (all sizes), first draft of third page (all sizes), full initial prototype if not complete</li>
  <li>April 22: Refined prototype</li>
  <li>April 29: Catch up week</li>
  <li>May 6: Due</li>
</ul>
